The recently appointed Brexit Opportunities Minister said he was inundated with recommendations after asking Britons which retained EU regulations should be abolished. Many mocked Mr Rees-Mogg upon the creation of the role, with Brendan O'Hara, SNP Cabinet Office spokesperson, joking he had been made “Secretary of State for Fantasy Island”. But the Tory MP has hit back, noting he has received 1,800 Brexit recommendations from readers of the Sun alone, “and I believe that the British people have an enormous amount of wisdom which politicians... could benefit from”. FOLLOW EXPRESS.CO.UK BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES: